HEADWORD: Bloodletting
<hw>Blood"let`ting</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The act or
process of letting blood or bleeding, as by opening a vein or artery, or
by cupping or leeches; -- esp. applied to venesection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

